After almost ten years, she moved to the Department of Music and Sonology at the University of Chile.
In 1980 she was appointed a full professor at that university.
In 1969 she joined the Ensemble of Ancient Music, a group created by Sylvia Soublette and Juana Subercaseaux at the Pontifical Catholic University.
In September 2010, she won the Chilean National Prize for Musical Arts, becoming the third member of her family to do so.
